00:45:02.120 --> 00:45:02.920
That's true

00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:11.240
Nikhil will not approve, I think

00:45:15.760 --> 00:45:16.920
But the thing is...

00:45:20.480 --> 00:45:22.120
I have in me...

00:45:25.920 --> 00:45:27.080
...a stubborn streak

00:45:29.320 --> 00:45:32.480
I can't accept Nikhil's attitude at all

00:45:35.320 --> 00:45:40.680
I want to spread the
cause of Swadeshi right here

00:45:42.400 --> 00:45:44.080
And I want your help

00:45:45.960 --> 00:45:48.440
But I really know
nothing about your work

00:45:48.880 --> 00:45:52.520
I know that you make
speeches Is that all?

00:45:54.760 --> 00:46:00.080
That's one of the main
things; persuasion can work wonders

00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:02.960
Wait.

00:46:05.080 --> 00:46:09.400
If you really want to know
about our work, read this

00:46:10.968 --> 00:46:12.400
You will know
everything when you read this.

00:46:12.480 --> 00:46:14.080
"Our Struggle"

00:46:18.120 --> 00:46:19.640
I'll certainly read it

00:46:21.668 --> 00:46:23.600
May I tell you something now?

00:46:25.177 --> 00:46:29.057
One of the biggest markets in
this area is here, in Suksayar

00:46:30.097 --> 00:46:31.378
So I've heard

00:46:31.897 --> 00:46:34.018
It's the only market in the district

00:46:34.537 --> 00:46:36.817
..where foreign goods
are still being sold

00:46:37.657 --> 00:46:41.017
Elsewhere the landowners
have stopped their sale

00:46:41.458 --> 00:46:42.658
But Nikhil hasn't done so

00:46:44.057 --> 00:46:46.138
I'll do my best to right that...

00:46:46.937 --> 00:46:50.657
...but with your help my
task would be much easier

00:46:51.457 --> 00:46:54.898
I'm afraid you
over-estimate my capabilities

00:46:55.099 --> 00:46:56.017
Not at all

00:46:57.617 --> 00:47:01.217
Nikhil may be my friend,
but he's your husband

00:47:01.858 --> 00:47:04.018
You have much more hold on him

00:47:04.738 --> 00:47:07.697
My husband is not easily swayed

00:47:08.698 --> 00:47:13.217
I know, but I think he'll listen to you

00:47:18.017 --> 00:47:20.698
I know how much you mean to him

00:47:21.977 --> 00:47:23.417
Will you try just once to persuade him?

00:47:26.857 --> 00:47:29.497
Nikhil's tenants would not
dare go against his will

00:47:30.097 --> 00:47:32.938
He has only to tell them not to
bring foreign goods into the market

00:47:34.337 --> 00:47:36.017
And if I fail to persuade him?

00:47:36.740 --> 00:47:39.137
I'd be happy if you only tried

00:47:40.574 --> 00:47:42.257
If you fail, I'll use other means

00:47:43.498 --> 00:47:45.538
Not without Queen
Bee's knowledge, of course

00:47:46.937 --> 00:47:49.138
Can I depend on you?

00:47:50.536 --> 00:47:51.778
I'll try

00:47:59.537 --> 00:48:00.977
The more I see you...

00:48:01.697 --> 00:48:03.857
...the more I'm filled with admiration

00:48:15.178 --> 00:48:16.138
I think I'll...

00:48:17.137 --> 00:48:18.977
You may go now

00:48:23.269 --> 00:48:24.257
Listen.

00:48:26.886 --> 00:48:28.457
There's something...

00:48:35.423 --> 00:48:39.983
This is one foreign
object which I shall keep

00:48:45.143 --> 00:48:47.103
Did you see Sandip today

00:48:48.623 --> 00:48:49.583
Yes

00:48:52.775 --> 00:48:53.863
How is he doing?

00:48:55.663 --> 00:48:57.343
He's worried

00:48:57.650 --> 00:48:58.303
Why?

00:49:00.623 --> 00:49:02.543
You don't take kindly to his Swadeshi

00:49:03.223 --> 00:49:04.583
Nonsense

00:49:05.063 --> 00:49:08.103
He's free to work for his cause...

00:49:08.743 --> 00:49:10.223
..as long as he leaves my estate alone

00:49:12.223 --> 00:49:14.183
He says he'll stay here

00:49:15.783 --> 00:49:16.783
Stay here?

00:49:18.223 --> 00:49:21.863
That's what he says;
stay here and work here

00:49:24.783 --> 00:49:26.063
That wouldn't be right

00:49:27.903 --> 00:49:31.023
But everyone has taken up
Swadeshi; why can't you?

00:49:31.983 --> 00:49:36.943
That notion would mean throwing
all foreign goods out of the market

00:49:37.967 --> 00:49:40.663
Harish Kundu can do that I can't

00:49:41.503 --> 00:49:43.783
Surely the market belongs to you

00:49:44.630 --> 00:49:48.743
No, Bimala, the market
belongs to the traders;

00:49:48.823 --> 00:49:51.143
.. they're people of small means

00:49:53.283 --> 00:49:57.743
Foreign goods are
cheaper and of better quality

00:50:00.072 --> 00:50:02.063
Naturally, the poor prefer to buy them.

00:50:02.383 --> 00:50:04.143
How can I force them not to?

00:50:06.712 --> 00:50:12.143
Swadeshi is for those who can afford it

00:50:17.371 --> 00:50:18.423
What are you thinking?

00:50:19.834 --> 00:50:21.343
Can't we have...

00:50:24.087 --> 00:50:26.927
...Swadeshi so that
the poor don't suffer?

00:50:28.171 --> 00:50:31.247
If we could, I'd certainly support it

00:50:32.487 --> 00:50:34.767
You think the very
idea of Swadeshi is wrong?

00:50:36.127 --> 00:50:40.727
Even if I do think it is wrong,
who will listen to me?

00:50:41.868 --> 00:50:43.967
You yourself felt that Sandip was right;

00:50:44.443 --> 00:50:46.207
...many others will feel the same

00:50:48.327 --> 00:50:54.167
But I believe that coercing the
poor can only harm the country

00:51:00.647 --> 00:51:02.527
I can see you're not convinced

00:51:03.967 --> 00:51:05.767
I was looking at it differently;

00:51:06.607 --> 00:51:09.487
I felt something had to be done

00:51:10.178 --> 00:51:13.887
Even if it meant hardship for the
poor now, it'll help in the long run

00:51:14.715 --> 00:51:17.447
Swadeshis do care for their country

00:51:18.978 --> 00:51:24.687
I believe that what they care for
is an abstract image of the country

00:51:25.196 --> 00:51:27.247
The country as the Mother Goddess

00:51:28.447 --> 00:51:29.767
Worship the Mother,

00:51:30.255 --> 00:51:34.847
...work for the Mother
dedicate your life to her sorrows

00:51:35.989 --> 00:51:40.949
I know the notion is
bound to appeal to women

00:51:42.469 --> 00:51:47.149
I know very well how you feel

00:51:48.149 --> 00:51:52.589
But I can't feel the same way

00:52:16.309 --> 00:52:20.469
What you were saying tonight
were they your own thoughts?

00:52:20.853 --> 00:52:22.389
Why this question?

00:52:23.149 --> 00:52:23.829
No.

00:52:24.989 --> 00:52:27.709
I felt you were speaking for Sandip

00:52:27.989 --> 00:52:30.589
Sandip is your friend, not mine

00:52:32.389 --> 00:52:36.909
I thought you had teamed up in
right earnest to work for the cause

00:52:38.149 --> 00:52:41.429
He working in public,
you on the domestic front

00:52:41.509 --> 00:52:42.709
What an idea!

00:52:50.989 --> 00:52:52.549
Will you have daily meetings?

00:52:53.549 --> 00:52:55.429
After pressing me to meet your friend,

00:52:55.509 --> 00:52:57.829
..you can spare me the insinuations

00:53:08.869 --> 00:53:09.869
Sorry, Bimala.

00:53:11.069 --> 00:53:15.709
I asked a simple question,
Bimala; I didn't insinuate anything

00:53:15.909 --> 00:53:19.149
Very well, if it upsets you so much,
I shall not go outside

00:53:20.709 --> 00:53:24.109
You're making a mistake
Why should I be upset?

00:53:25.273 --> 00:53:30.607
After all, I know you both so well,
and why shouldn't you go out?

00:53:30.684 --> 00:53:32.469
Because I don't want to

00:53:33.822 --> 00:53:35.341
You're being unreasonable

00:53:35.422 --> 00:53:38.302
I've been out twice; I
don't have to go out every day

00:53:41.489 --> 00:53:42.582
Very well

00:53:52.782 --> 00:53:54.822
I don't mind if you go or don't go.

00:53:55.662 --> 00:53:57.222
I shall not force you

00:53:59.022 --> 00:54:03.142
I've told you you're
free to do as you please

00:54:04.734 --> 00:54:08.221
But I must tell you one thing

00:54:10.662 --> 00:54:14.382
If you say you'll give up
wearing foreign clothes...

00:54:15.262 --> 00:54:19.422
...or do without your perfumes,
your shoes, your soap...

00:54:20.302 --> 00:54:24.622
...I won't mind at all

00:54:26.622 --> 00:54:29.262
But clamping down on poor traders..

00:54:30.550 --> 00:54:32.749
..means abandoning a
principle I hold dear

00:54:33.990 --> 00:54:35.470
That I can never do

00:54:42.390 --> 00:54:45.469
Swadeshi is something
I can't take lightly

00:54:52.110 --> 00:54:54.349
The weak say:

00:54:54.790 --> 00:55:00.109
that which has
fallen to my share is mine

00:55:00.870 --> 00:55:03.310
And the impotent assent, but
the lesson of experience is;

00:55:03.589 --> 00:55:05.269
only that which I can
snatch away by force is mine

00:55:06.109 --> 00:55:10.390
My country is not mine
simply because I was born here

00:55:10.470 --> 00:55:14.749
It becomes mine only when I
am able to win it by force

00:55:20.590 --> 00:55:22.750
The funeral pyre
celebrates the last rites...

00:55:23.470 --> 00:55:27.390
...of foreign commerce in your village

00:55:28.110 --> 00:55:29.869
These ashes are sacred

00:55:30.630 --> 00:55:32.310
Hail Motherland!

00:55:32.389 --> 00:55:34.510
Hail Motherland !

00:55:34.590 --> 00:55:36.150
Hail Motherland !

00:55:36.229 --> 00:55:38.550
Hail Motherland !

00:55:46.892 --> 00:55:52.270
An urgent matter. Touching the cause

00:56:02.989 --> 00:56:04.669
Please give this to Mrs. Choudhury

00:56:05.142 --> 00:56:06.150
Okay.

00:56:46.819 --> 00:56:48.780
Madam is unwell, Sir

00:56:53.570 --> 00:56:54.420
I see

00:57:05.899 --> 00:57:07.819
You know the Headmaster, don't you?

00:57:09.139 --> 00:57:11.740
Good morning. I hope you are well

00:57:13.380 --> 00:57:14.940
Not while you're about

00:57:19.446 --> 00:57:20.500
How is that?

00:57:21.134 --> 00:57:24.060
His students have
disappeared since you arrived

00:57:25.827 --> 00:57:31.459
But you must admit that to work for
one's country helps to shape character

00:57:33.830 --> 00:57:39.190
One of my students hit Mrs.
Choudhury's governess,

00:57:39.270 --> 00:57:41.350
Miss Gilby, with a stone

00:57:42.430 --> 00:57:45.550
Does that, too, come
under shaping character?

00:57:45.630 --> 00:57:51.230
But that was before I came
here; you can't blame me for that

00:57:51.554 --> 00:57:54.830
And you must admit that
such stray incidents...

00:57:54.910 --> 00:57:58.950
...are inevitable in times of upheaval

00:57:59.590 --> 00:58:02.350
You've roped in my
best student, haven't you?

00:58:02.529 --> 00:58:03.485
Who?

00:58:03.562 --> 00:58:04.710
Amulya? - Yes.

00:58:06.030 --> 00:58:09.270
He'd have won a
scholarship if he'd sat his exam.

00:58:09.870 --> 00:58:11.190
You prevented him

00:58:11.270 --> 00:58:14.590
Amulya? I didn't rope him in,
he joined of his own accord

00:58:14.870 --> 00:58:22.030
And what about our rowdies and
shirkers? They've joined, too

00:58:22.510 --> 00:58:24.910
They're not shirkers any more, sir;

00:58:25.030 --> 00:58:27.230
..they're working for the cause

00:58:28.190 --> 00:58:31.670
With two exceptions, everyone
here is working for the cause

00:58:32.070 --> 00:58:37.910
The exceptions are you
and your ex-student Nikhil

00:58:38.350 --> 00:58:41.430
I regret that I
couldn't persuade him to join

00:58:41.630 --> 00:58:44.190
Like you, he turns a
deaf ear to Swadeshi

00:58:44.270 --> 00:58:50.790
No, only to your brand
of destructive Swadeshi

00:58:51.870 --> 00:58:53.990
He practiced Swadeshi
long before your time

00:58:54.150 --> 00:58:59.270
And he needed no battle-cries
to bolster him. You know nothing

00:58:59.750 --> 00:59:01.710
Do you know of his Swadeshi bank?

00:59:01.892 --> 00:59:04.870
Of his sugar factory, his soap factory?

00:59:05.255 --> 00:59:09.910
Do you know he set up his own
looms for weaving Swadeshi cloth?

00:59:10.791 --> 00:59:15.390
Where were you and your
Hail Motherland! then?

00:59:15.983 --> 00:59:18.347
Do you know how much he
spent on his Swadeshi?

00:59:18.628 --> 00:59:20.028
Do you know something?
- It is okay, sir.

00:59:20.104 --> 00:59:22.750
You stay out of this!
These things must be told

00:59:23.070 --> 00:59:27.470
But that's just what I tell him;
if you and I have the same aim...

00:59:27.547 --> 00:59:29.341
...why not join us?

00:59:29.418 --> 00:59:32.670
It's no the same aim at all

00:59:33.238 --> 00:59:37.396
You aim to be self-seeking leaders;

00:59:37.551 --> 00:59:39.150
you don't think of the people at all

00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:41.981
Nikhil's devotion was selfless

00:59:42.461 --> 00:59:46.581
You are being feted

00:59:47.820 --> 00:59:49.380
Nikhil was ridiculed

00:59:50.186 --> 00:59:54.660
he had no head for business,
so his Swadeshi didn't last

00:59:54.780 --> 00:59:58.821
But his was the right way Yours is wrong

00:59:59.021 --> 01:00:02.340
It's more than wrong; it's harmful

01:00:02.861 --> 01:00:03.581
Dangerous.

01:00:05.149 --> 01:00:05.820
Give it to me.

01:00:07.901 --> 01:00:09.621
I'll drop by in the evening

01:00:14.541 --> 01:00:15.461
Oh my God.

01:00:19.461 --> 01:00:25.181
I implore you, Nikhil, keep
that headmaster out of my way

01:00:25.665 --> 01:00:27.821
I've come here to make speeches

01:00:28.020 --> 01:00:29.421
...not to suffer them

01:00:30.990 --> 01:00:33.341
I believe you're
planning to stay here and work

01:00:39.946 --> 01:00:43.620
I'm going to speak in
your market this afternoon

01:00:45.686 --> 01:00:47.340
That's where the challenge is

01:00:49.221 --> 01:00:53.820
Not where the land owner
himself supports Swadeshi

01:00:55.821 --> 01:00:56.820
Not there.

01:00:57.621 --> 01:01:02.340
But remember: most of my
tenants are poor muslims

01:01:04.379 --> 01:01:08.580
I don't want them to be harassed

01:01:10.620 --> 01:01:15.261
If I see that happening, I
will be forced to intervene

01:01:16.500 --> 01:01:21.540
If they prove to be stubborn,
I shall have to take measures

01:01:22.491 --> 01:01:24.611
many Muslims have accepted Swadeshi

01:01:25.410 --> 01:01:27.291
They've been compelled to...

01:01:28.530 --> 01:01:29.691
It'll happen here

01:01:33.771 --> 01:01:39.810
I've said what had to.
What you do now is up to you

01:01:46.382 --> 01:01:50.462
You all know that the
British have by law ...

01:01:50.942 --> 01:01:54.382
... divided Bengal into two

01:01:55.222 --> 01:02:01.782
This amounts to erecting a
wall between Hindus and Muslims

01:02:02.662 --> 01:02:07.702
They have not given us the
right to break this wall

01:02:08.063 --> 01:02:11.982
But to foil the government we
have chosen a different path

01:02:12.368 --> 01:02:14.622
One important way ...

01:02:14.964 --> 01:02:20.142
... is to stop selling
foreign goods in our markets

01:02:20.702 --> 01:02:26.142
The things you sell : salt, sugar,
cloth, articles of daily use ...

01:02:26.222 --> 01:02:29.422
... are all foreign products

01:02:30.126 --> 01:02:37.343
Because you sell them,
foreigners grow rich ...

01:02:37.663 --> 01:02:41.662
... and Indians become poor

01:02:42.262 --> 01:02:44.382
This is wrong, it must not go on

01:02:44.902 --> 01:02:48.302
So far we have
tolerated this, but no more

01:02:48.782 --> 01:02:54.262
Indian substitutes for foreign
goods are not always available

01:02:54.822 --> 01:02:58.942
So you have had to
trade in what there is

01:02:59.462 --> 01:03:06.102
If we make sacrifices and
produce Indian goods ...

01:03:06.502 --> 01:03:09.942
... we shall overcome these difficulties

01:03:10.342 --> 01:03:13.582
Friends, come forward ...

01:03:14.222 --> 01:03:18.822
... so that we may avoid the
division of Bengal and we may regain ...

01:03:19.022 --> 01:03:20.902
... our self-esteem

01:03:21.822 --> 01:03:26.102
See this circle before me

01:03:26.262 --> 01:03:31.302
Throw your foreign goods
into the circle of flags

01:03:32.142 --> 01:03:35.262
Indian substitutes will be made

01:03:35.822 --> 01:03:38.782
Manufacturers have come forward

01:03:39.302 --> 01:03:42.462
Do not fear of losing your livelihood

01:03:42.862 --> 01:03:46.262
Today's loss will not be lost for ever

01:03:46.763 --> 01:03:50.582
Get rid of your foreign goods

01:03:51.542 --> 01:03:56.182
The land that gave you birth,
the land that you love ...

01:03:56.393 --> 01:03:59.022
... help that land

01:03:59.172 --> 01:04:02.622
Cloth from foreign mills, sugar ...

01:04:02.858 --> 01:04:05.982
... salt, soap ...

01:04:06.422 --> 01:04:09.702
... scissors and knives ...

01:04:10.062 --> 01:04:13.622
Surrender them in the
noble cause of Swadeshi

01:04:14.350 --> 01:04:17.630
We beseech you : don't just sit there

01:04:17.710 --> 01:04:20.110
Come ahead and help in
the cause of Swadeshi.

01:04:20.190 --> 01:04:24.150
Let the Maharaja come and tell us

01:04:24.548 --> 01:04:25.950
We won't listen to you

01:04:27.630 --> 01:04:32.030
Your Maharaja is my friend.
I am his guest

01:04:32.590 --> 01:04:35.550
Isn't that proof enough
that I have his support ?

01:04:35.630 --> 01:04:38.434
If we poor traders have
nothing to sell, we'll starve

01:04:38.510 --> 01:04:43.100
We've tried selling
Indian goods. Nobody buys them

01:04:43.177 --> 01:04:44.270
You have money.

01:04:44.350 --> 01:04:49.150
It's easy for you to say
don't sell foreign goods

01:04:49.630 --> 01:04:52.110
We're poor. How can we
live without our trade ?

01:04:58.254 --> 01:05:00.950
It's clear that persuasion
won't work in Nikhil's estate

01:05:01.630 --> 01:05:03.550
We have to use other means

01:05:04.150 --> 01:05:08.630
Any compromise would
cripple our movement

